Note:
One of the key advantages of building your weather forecast system with Arduino Uno is its flexibility to accommodate a wide range of sensors. 
**You can add as many sensors as you desire to gather comprehensive data about the environment.**
The source code provided in this guide is designed to be easily configurable, allowing you to integrate new sensors seamlessly. 
Simply follow the guidelines provided in the documentation for each sensor type and adjust the code accordingly to read and process the additional data.
Experiment with different sensor combinations to tailor your weather forecast system to your specific needs and preferences. 
The possibilities are virtually endless, empowering you to create a truly customizable and robust solution for weather prediction.
